The draw for the Copa del Rey semi-final has been announced. The draw was announced at the headquarters of the Royal Spanish Football Federation on Friday in Spain following the conclusion of the quarter-final stage on Thursday night. Real Sociedad defeated Real Madrid 4-3 last night, while Athletic Bilbao won Barcelona 1-0. Granada defeated Valencia 2-1, while Mirandes won Villarreal 4-2. The two-legged fixtures will take place on February 11 or 12 and the second on March 3 or 4. Below is the Copa del Rey last four draws in full: Real Sociedad vs. Mirandes Granada vs. Athletic Club The Copa del Rey final is scheduled for 18 April 2020.